search::displayResults()

Description
    private string search::displayResults(array $results)
    Generates HTML to display the results of a submission.

Parameters
    results
	An array of results returned from a successful MySQL query.

Return Values
    Returns a string containing HTML.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	foreach ($this->searchArray as $searchType => $keywords) {
	    $sql = $this->createQuery($searchType,$keywords);
	    if (debugNeeded("query")) {
		print "<br />".htmlSanitize($sql)."<br /><br />";
	    }
	    $this->engine->openDB->sanitize = FALSE;
	    $sqlResult = $this->engine->openDB->query($sql);
	    $results[] = $sqlResult['result'];
	}
		
	$output .= $this->displayResults($results);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    search::submit()
